IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: The organization's primary exempt purpose is to provide health and supportive services to seniors living at home who meet the State of Florida, Department of Elder Affairs' requirements for nursing home level care. Through its multi-disciplinary team, the PACE program is responsible for coordinating and contracting to provide medical, in-patient and out-patient hospital services, pharmacy and in-home services.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Chief Financial Officer and Controller conduct a comprehensive review of the Form 990 before it is filed. A copy of the return, as ultimately filed, is provided to both Audit Committee members, and each voting member of the Board of Directors prior to it being filed with the IRS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization's conflict of interest policy covers all board members, physicians on staff and key employees, each of whom is required to complete and submit a conflict of interest questionnaire annually. The Chief Compliance Officer monitors and enforces compliance with the conflict of interest policy and reviews actual conflicts that are identified by the annual disclosure process. Officers and directors are prohibited from voting on matters where actual conflicts of interest exist.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Board of Directors determines the compensation and benefits of the Chief Executive Officer. Compensation and benefits of other top management officials is determined by the Chief Executive Officer. All individuals are independent with respect to compensation arrangements being considered and utilized comparability surveys provided by Human Resources department. The review and approval process is documented in board minutes.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements available for public inspection upon request.
The organization is a subsidiary of Miami Jewish Health Systems, Inc. Its financial statements were audited as part of a consolidated financial statement.

The Audit Committee has responsibility for the oversight of audit, related income tax filing reviews and selection of an independent accountant. There was no change in this process from the prior year.
